Supporters are flocking to Ace Magashule's stomping ground in Bloemfontein. Some are dressed in ANC party regalia, openly defying the ruling party's directive not to support alleged corrupt officials in court in party colours. Magashule faces charges of corruption linked to the Free State's asbestos saga. eNCA's Thulasizwe Simelane, Siphamandla Goge and Aviwe Mtila are monitoring developments. Courtesy #DStv403 BLOEMFONTEIN - Supporters are flocking to Ace Magashule's stomping ground in Bloemfontein. Some are dressed in ANC party regalia, openly defying the ruling party's directive not to support alleged corrupt officials in court in party colours. READ: Magashule supporters hold night vigil ahead of court appearance The ANC Secretary-General is one of the people accused of corruption in connection with the R225-million asbestos audit project. He is expected to hand himself over shortly. ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule is expected to hand himself over shortly. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila spoke to MKMVA spokesperson Carl Niehaus. Courtesy #DStv403